                  </persName>
            . I am Mr. Luckin's son. While he was trying on the shoes his back was turned. I saw the prisoner put his hand into the glass case, take a pair of shoes, and put them under his jacket; he said he would call for the shoes next day, and walked backwards to the door. I went up and laid hold of him - he ran across the close, and I saw the shoes fall from him - he was secured.</p>

               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>

               <p>Prisoner. I wanted to pay for them.</p>
